original:
Middle Eastern thought has been significantly influenced by a variety of cultural and intellectual movements, particularly in Lebanon. Beirut emerged as a vibrant center for Armenian culture, producing diverse artistic works that were disseminated throughout the Armenian diaspora.


The development of visual arts in Lebanon saw the emergence of several notable artists. Daoud Corm (1852-1930), Habib Serour (1860-1938), and Khalil Saleeby
